Package: matilda
Type: Package
Title: Multi-Task Learning from Single-Cell Multimodal Omics
Version: 0.99.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Chunlei", "Liu", role = "aut", email = "chunlei@cmri.com"),
    person("Pengyi", "Yang", role = "aut"),
    person("Sichang", "Ding", role = "cre", email = "usyddsc@gmail.com"))
Description: R interface to Matilda, a multi-task framework for single-cell
    multimodal omics (RNA, ADT, ATAC). Trains a multimodal variational
    autoencoder plus classifier and runs cell-type classification, dimension
    reduction, feature selection and data simulation. The original PyTorch
    implementation is wrapped via 'reticulate' inside a 'basilisk'-managed
    environment and operates on SingleCellExperiment and MultiAssayExperiment
    objects, writing results back into the object.
